The stercomare is extensively developed and fills most of the test interior (Supplementary 
Fig. S10E, F
), but does not conform to any clear pattern. Irregularly shaped masses, usually several hundred microns in size, often merge into and are connected byirregular branches, ranging from around 30 to 70 µm in often of uneven width. Strands of the granellare system can be found between these masses. They are whitish and 20 to 65 µm in width, although sometimes forming larger masses>100 µm in size. There are no obvious internal xenophyae.

