The test is attached to a nodule at its base. There is no distinct stalk, but the attachment area appears to be fairly restricted. Root-like extensions arise from the base of the test in several of the photographs. In one image, a main trunk, much paler than the main part of the test, extends down the side of the nodule before dividing into several branches (Supplementary 
Fig. S11F
