sec.p:
This new collection builds on previous studies of xenophyophores in the eastern Clarion-Clipperton Zone (
, b, c, 2018), as well as the central (Kamenskaya 2005; Kamenskaya et al ., 2015, 2017) and western part (
, b) of the CCZ . We recognised a total of 18 species and obtained sequences from eight of them. Three of those that were sequenced were new to science (two assigned to new genera), three were assigned to known species, and two were described under open nomenclature. The ten species from which no sequences were obtained included one that was previously described (
P. multiloculata
) and nine that were left under open nomenclature, four of them previously unknown. The newly described species increases the number of named xenophyophore species found in the CCZ from the current total of 24 (
) to 27, and the total number in the CCZ , both described and undescribed, from 63 to 70.
